  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="egov-faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="sect-head">

        <h2 class="egov-h2">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>
      <!-- TODO-WG: verify each Q&A pairing and all compliance/client claims (ISO version, certifications, named bodies) before publishing. -->
      <div class="faq-wrap">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What is IT staff augmentation for public sector projects in India?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>IT staff augmentation for public sector projects means deploying vetted, background-verified technology professionals within Central Ministries, State Departments, or PSUs to supplement in-house delivery teams. Procurement is typically routed through GeM manpower supply categories, department-issued bids on CPPP, or subcontracting under prime vendors. Webority Technologies operates this as a managed delivery service — not a transactional staffing arrangement — with profile interviews accommodated before mobilisation, structured onboarding, and a written replacement SLA.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Can departments procure Webority’s IT manpower through GeM?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. Webority Technologies is registered on the Government e-Marketplace (GeM) under manpower supply categories applicable to IT roles. Departments and PSUs can procure directly via Buy on GeM for short-duration or below-threshold needs, or include Webority in standard GeM bids and CPPP tenders for longer engagements (the standard public sector contract is 12 months, with extension clauses). For prime-vendor engagements, we supply professionals under standard subcontracting arrangements.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How does Webority handle the buyer-interview clause in GeM bids?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Every profile we propose is interview-ready. When a tender includes a buyer-interview clause — which is standard in most public sector IT manpower bids — we make the candidate available for the department’s technical and HR rounds before deployment. If a profile is not selected, we supply replacement candidates for re-interview at no additional cost or delay to the procurement timeline.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What is the standard mobilisation timeline after work order issuance?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>5–10 working days from work order issuance for standard profiles — including background verification, onboarding documentation, induction briefing on department processes, and security clearance preparation where required. For specialised profiles such as DevSecOps, AI/ML, or Solution Architects, 2–3 weeks may be required depending on availability. Urgent mobilisation is supported from our pre-vetted bench of profiles already cleared for public sector deployment.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What experience bands and qualifications does Webority cover?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>All GeM standard experience bands — Less than 1 year, 1 to less than 3 years, 3 to less than 5 years, 5 to less than 8 years, and 8 years and above. Qualifications cover the full GeM standard set: BE / B.Tech (Computer Science, IT, Electronics), MCA, M.Tech, M.Sc. (CS / IT). Profile selection is matched line-by-line to the tender’s specific experience and qualification clauses.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Which technology stacks does Webority supply for public sector tenders?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>The most frequently requested public sector stacks are all available: PHP / Laravel + MySQL (the standard GeM full-stack profile, including PSR standards, REST APIs, jQuery, Bootstrap, HTML5/CSS3); Java / Spring Boot + Oracle for NIC-style platforms; Python / Django + PostgreSQL for analytics and data platforms; .NET (C#) + MS SQL for legacy modernisation; React, Angular, Vue for frontend; Flutter and React Native for mobile; and DevOps profiles covering Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, GitLab CI, and MeghRaj migration. Functional domain expertise includes Payment Gateway Integration, India Stack (Aadhaar, DigiLocker, UPI), GIGW 3.0, WCAG 2.1 AA, CPGRAMS, PFMS, DBT, and eOffice.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What happens if a deployed resource leaves or under-performs?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Webority Technologies provides a written replacement SLA on every engagement. If a deployed professional is unable to continue or does not meet performance expectations, a replacement profile of equivalent or higher experience is supplied within the SLA window agreed at contract signing — typically 7–15 working days. Knowledge transfer is managed by Webority to ensure no continuity loss to the department’s project. This accountability is the core difference between our managed delivery model and a transactional staffing arrangement.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

